            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(S.N.) In nomine domini. Brevis recordationis, qualiter vel in quorum
                        presencia <rs key="#Marquis/duke">domina et comitissa</rs>
                        <persName key="#Marquis/duke" ref="#people/125">Matildis</persName>, filia
                        quondam <persName ref="#people/1" key="#Marquis/duke">Bonifacii</persName>,
                        qui fuit <rs key="#Marquis/duke">dux et marchio</rs>, fecit conventionem cum
                            <rs key="#Abbesses">abbatissa</rs>
                        <persName ref="#people/1601" key="#Abbesses">Imelda</persName> de <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/53"><rs key="#Monasteries"
                                >monasterio</rs> sanctorum Xisti et Fabiani</orgName>, quod est
                        hedificatum <placeName ref="#places/43">Placencie</placeName>, nominative de
                            <rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs> et <rs key="#Castle">castro</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/33"
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Profits_of_justice #Districtio #Feudum"
                                ><geogName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Profits_of_justice #Districtio #Feudum"
                                ref="#estates/40">Wadestalle</geogName></placeName>, sicut dividitur
                        ab <rs key="#Dioecesis">episcopatu</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/58" key="#Dioecesis">Cremonensi</placeName> ultra
                            <rs key="#Rivers">Padum</rs> et citra, et sicut distinguitur inter
                            <geogName key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                            ref="#estates/38">curtem <placeName ref="#places/32"
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                                >Luciarie</placeName></geogName> et per totum decursum <rs
                            key="#Rivers">Gurgi</rs> et eius decursiones in <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >Bundinum</rs>, item sicut dividitur ab episcopatu <placeName
                            ref="#places/53" key="#Dioecesis">Parmensi</placeName> per flumen <rs
                            key="#Rivers">Distisi</rs> et Bundini cum eius decursione usque ad locum
                        crucis, ut ab hac hora inantea habeat iam dictum monasterium predictum
                        castrum et curtem ita prefatam cum omni <rs key="#Census">pensione</rs> et
                            <rs key="#Public_exactions">conditione</rs>, quod de ipso castro exierit
                        pro investitura ipsius castri et curtis. Et si aliquis offenderit in ipso
                        castro de furto vel traditione ipsius castri, abbatissa vel eius successor
                        habeat <rs key="#Profits_of_justice #Districtio">potestatem emendandi</rs>;
                        si vero aliquis aliter offenderit in ipso castro et curte, si de foris
                        habuerit, ipsa domina Matildis vel suus <rs key="#Missus">missus</rs>
                        emendet. Curtem vero et omnia <rs key="#Feudum">feuda</rs> de his, qui sunt
                        de foris, hominibus et cetera in integrum post meum decessum habeat iam
                        dictum monasterium. Etiam hoc convenit inter eos, ut nulli alii ab hac die
                        inantea aliquid ipsius castri vel curtis dare debeat iam dicta domina
                        Matildis de hoc, quod habeat in suo <rs key="#Demesnes">domnicato</rs> vel
                        curte. Factum est hoc anno dominice incarnationis MC secundo, IIII die
                        mensis iunii, indictione decima, in loco, qui dicitur <placeName
                            ref="#places/1910">Mirandula</placeName>. Ibi fuerunt <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Obizo de Parpanese">Opizo de
                            Parpanese</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Aluartus">Aluardus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"
                                ><name ref="Iohannes Engelbardi">Iohannes
                            Engelbardi</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Sigitius de monasterio">Sigezo de monasterio</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Belencionus"
                            >Belencionus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Lanfrancus">Lanfrancus</name></persName>,<persName
                            key="#Witness"> Iohannes Bonus</persName> et <persName
                            key="#Witness #Deacons"><name ref="Iohannes filius Iohannis">Iohannes
                                filius Iohannis</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Deacons">diaconi</rs>, <persName key="#Witness">Martinus
                            Biuinus</persName>. + Matilda dei gratia, si quid est, subscripsi (S.
                        N.) Ego <persName key="#Professional_writer #Judge"><name ref="Iohannes"
                                >Iohannes</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Professional_writer #Judge">iudex sacri palacii</rs> rogatus
                        subscripsi.</ab>
